<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Colin Weaver (HCS0004)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from Colin Weaver (HCS0004)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Excessive Noise in Helicopters causing Crew </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">issues ?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">As I have explained in another note, I worked in the Oil Industry for many years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">What always struck me on the big Helicopters like the Super Puma was the very high noise level in the passenger </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">compartment, even whilst wearing a headset and foam ear plugs.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">From my experience in my early days working in an Oil Refinery Power Station, and later on visiting Oil Platforms, is that even with ear protection, that somehow excessive noise impedes concen</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tration, and possibly spatial awareness.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In that helicopters are built to a weight limit (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ie</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> flimsy), and that the 15 (</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ish</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">) seat helicopters have very powerful and noisy engines, and a gearbox or two whirring away, along with the rotor blade vortex noise,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> I wonder what it is like to be continually exposed to this noise as a Pilot. The crew also have only a plastic windscreen canopy to shield them from noise, along with their headset.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In addition, helicopters can create very low frequency noise, some of wh</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ich can be felt rather than heard, and which is very difficult to attenuate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I would suggest that some sort of study of the effects of these very high noise levels on pilot performance (and potential hearing loss) is carried out, especially at the end of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a shift.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_GoBack"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Liberation Serif'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>